{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"34ff9a56-9443-48a5-b576-36854768388c","content":"For a .NET Web API project, use the **`webapi`** template:\n\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi -n MyApi\n```\n\n### Authentication Options (`--auth`)\n\n| Option | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `None` | No authentication (default) |\n| `IndividualB2C` | Azure AD B2C individual accounts |\n| `SingleOrg` | Single-tenant Azure AD (organizational) |\n| `MultiOrg` | Multi-tenant Azure AD |\n| `Windows` | Windows/Negotiate authentication |\n\n### Examples\n\n```bash\n# Azure AD single-org auth\ndotnet new webapi --auth SingleOrg --domain example.com --tenant-id <id> --client-id <id>\n\n# Azure AD B2C\ndotnet new webapi --auth IndividualB2C\n\n# Minimal API with OpenAPI support (default in .NET 8+)\ndotnet new webapi --use-minimal-apis\n```\n\nFor JWT bearer auth without Azure AD, start with `--auth None` and add `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authentication.JwtBearer` manually. You can also consider the **`webapi-aot`** template for a native AOT-optimized minimal API.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"56166360-7ee4-4ce7-8b09-dae00002d2fb","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about web API project templates and authentication options. This is a general knowledge question about .NET (likely, given the repository context with dotnet plugins). I can answer this from my knowledge without needing to search the codebase.","outputTokens":352,"requestId":"9C0B:3BE8A6:1CDF7D3:2057211:6A07BFC1"},"id":"4d45e291-87ba-4980-9217-b8d96ffb97db","timestamp":"2026-05-16T00:52:26.143Z","parentId":"304cf23c-282a-4ae1-b292-87c2dc83573a"}
